    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix DRB modification item processing in E1AP bearer context handling\n\n### Summary\nThe E1AP bearer context modification request handler in the CU-UP contains two critical bugs where assignment operators were used instead of comparison operators in DevAssert statements. This causes the values being checked to be unintentionally modified, leading to incorrect DRB configuration processing.\n\nWhen processing DRB to modify items, the code would incorrectly set the `present` fields of ASN.1 choice structures instead of just checking them, causing malformed DRB configurations to be applied. This results in failed bearer context modifications and potential connection drops for UEs.\n\nThe issue manifests as failed E1AP bearer context modification procedures when the CU-CP sends DRB reconfiguration requests with specific transport layer parameters.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Fixed assignment operators to comparison operators in DevAssert statements at lines 1359 and 1387 in the `extract_BEARER_CONTEXT_MODIFICATION_REQUEST` function.\n\n"
}